Basic Package Management Commands (RHEL / CentOS / Rocky / AlmaLinux)
➤ 1.1 Check OS Details
cat /etc/redhat-release


✔ Helps identify RHEL version for compatible packages.

➤ 1.2 Search for a Package
yum search httpd


✔ Search for any package available in repositories.

➤ 1.3 Install a Package
sudo yum install httpd -y


✔ Installs Apache web server.

➤ 1.4 Remove/Uninstall a Package
sudo yum remove httpd -y

➤ 1.5 Update a Specific Package
sudo yum update openssl

➤ 1.6 Update Entire System
sudo yum update -y


✔ Applies all security patches.

➤ 1.7 Check Installed Packages
rpm -qa
rpm -qa | grep httpd

➤ 1.8 Get Package Info
rpm -qi httpd

➤ 1.9 List Files Installed by a Package
rpm -ql httpd


✔ Helps find config file paths.

➤ 1.10 Verify Integrity of Package
rpm -V coreutils

➤ 1.11 Find Which Package Provides a File
yum provides /usr/bin/zip
